31994 [[Autozam Scrum]] [[microvan]] ([[Suzuki Carry]])\n* 1991\u20131994 [[Mazda MX-3|Autozam AZ-3]] [[coupe]] (Mazda MX-3)\n* 1992\u20131993 [[Mazda Capella|Autozam Clef]] [[sedan (car)|sedan]] (Mazda Capella)\n* 1992\u20131994 [[Autozam AZ-1]] [[Mid-engine design|mid-engine]] [[sports car]]\n\n===[[\u025b\u0303fini]]===\n* 1990\u20131997 [[Mazda MPV|\u025b\u0303fini MPV]] (Mazda MPV)\n* 1991\u20131993 [[Mazda Capella#GE (1991\u20131997)|\u025b\u0303fini MS-6]] ([[Mazda Cronos]])\n* 1992\u20131997 [[\u025b\u0303fini MS-8]]\n* 1991\u20131993 [[Mazda 929|\u025b\u0303fini MS-9]] (Mazda 929)\n* 1991\u20131996 [[Mazda RX-7|\u025b\u0303fini RX-7]] (Mazda RX-7)\n\n===[[Eunos (automobile)|Eunos]]===\n* 1989 [[Mazda Familia Astina|Eunos 100]] ([[Mazda Familia#1989-1994 (Mazda 323, 323F and Proteg\u00e9)|Mazda Familia]] [[Mazda B platform#BG|BG platform]])\n* 1989 [[Mazda Persona|Eunos 300]] (Mazda Persona [[Mazda M platform#MA|MA platform]])\n* 1992\u20131993 [[Mazda Xedos 6|Eunos 500]] (Mazda Xedos 6 [[Mazda C platform#CA|CA platform]])\n* 1993\u20131996 [[Mazda Millenia|Eunos 800]] (Mazda Millenia TA platform)\n* 1990 [[Mazda Bongo|Eunos Cargo]] ([[Mazda S platform#SS|SS platform]])\n* 1990\u20131991 [[Mazda Cosmo|Eunos Cosmo]] (Mazda Cosmo [[Mazda J platform#JC|JC platform]])\n* 1991\u20131993 [[Mazda MX-3|Eunos Presso/Eunos 30X]] (Mazda MX-3 [[Mazda E platform#EC|EC platform]])\n* 1989\u20131996 [[Mazda MX-5|Eunos Roadster]] (Mazda MX-5 [[Mazda N platform#NA|NA platform]])\n\n=== [[Xedos]] ===\n* 1993\u20131999 [[Mazda Xedos 6|Xedos 6]] (Eunos 500)\n* 1993\u20132002 [[Mazda Millenia|Xedos 9]] (Mazda Millenia)\n\n== See also ==\n* [[List of Mazda platforms]]\n* [[List of Mazda engines]]\n* [[Mazda]]\n\n{{Mazda vehicles}}\n{{Mazda}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:List Of Mazda Vehicles}}\n[[Category:Mazda vehicles|*]]\n[[Category:Lists of cars|Mazda]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\nThis is a list of [[Mazda]] [[Motor vehicle|motor vehicle]] models. Most Mazda vehicles have a different name for the Japan home market than is used in the rest of the world. Both names are included below, though the (often more consistent) Japanese names are often primary.\n\nMazda has used a number of different [[marque]]s in the Japan market, including [[Autozam]], [[Eunos (automobile)|Eunos]], and [[Efini]], although they have been phased out. In the early 1990s Mazda almost created a luxury marque, [[Amati Cars|Amati]], to challenge [[Acura]], [[Infiniti]], and [[Lexus]] in North America, but this never happened, leaving the near-luxury [[Mazda Millenia|Millenia]] to the Mazda brand.\n\nMany Mazda vehicles have been [[rebadge]]d and sold as [[Ford Motor Company|Ford]]s. Most are noted in the pages of individual vehicles.\n\nCurrent sports models of Mazda's regular vehicles go by the [[Mazdaspeed]] name. Mazdaspeed is Mazda's in-house race and street car tuning arm and is highly involved in both amateur and professional motorsports.\n==Current products==\nThis is the current Mazda automobile listing internationally.\n\n===[[Kei car]]===\n* [[Mazda Carol|Carol]] \u2014 [[hatchback]] ([[Rebadging|badge-engineered]] [[Suzuki Alto]])\n* [[Autozam Scrum|Scrum]] \u2014 [[minivan]] and [[van|commercial van]] (badge-engineered [[Suzuki Carry|Suzuki Carry/Every]])\n* [[Mazda Flair|Flair]] \u2014 minivan (badge-engineered [[Suzuki Wagon R]])\n* [[Mazda Flair Wagon|Flair Wagon]] \u2014 minivan (badge-engineered [[Suzuki Spacia]])\n* [[Mazda Flair Crossover|Flair Crossover]] \u2014 [[Crossover (automobile)|Crossover SUV]] (badge-engineered [[Suzuki Hustler]])\n\n===[[Subcompact car|Subcompact]]===\n* [[Mazda Demio|Mazda2/Demio]] \u2014 hatchback and [[Sedan (automobile)|sedan]]\n\n===[[Compact car|Compact]]===\n* [[Mazda3|Mazda3/Axela]] \u2014 hatchback and sedan\n\n===[[Mid-size car|Mid-size]]===\n* [[Mazda6|Mazda6/Atenza]] \u2014 sedan and [[Station wagon|wagon]]\n\n===[[Sports car]]===\n* [[Mazda MX-5|MX-5/Roadster]] \u2014 [[Roadster (automobile)|roadster]]\n\n===[[Sport utility vehicle|SUV]]===\n* [[Mazda CX-3|CX-3]] \u2014 subcompact crossover SUV\n* [[Mazda CX-30|CX-30]] \u2014 compact crossover SUV\n* [[Mazda MX-30|MX-30]] \u2014 compact electric crossover SUV\n* [[Mazda CX-4|CX-4]] \u2014 compact crossover SUV (China)\n* [[Mazda CX-5|CX-5]] \u2014 compact crossover SUV\n* [[Mazda CX-8|CX-8]] \u2014 lengthened compact crossover SUV (Japan, Australia, and Malaysia)\n* [[Mazda CX-9|CX-9]] \u2014 mid-size SUV\n\n===[[Pickup truck]]===\n* [[Mazda BT-50|BT-50]] \u2014 badge-engineered [[Ford Ranger (T6)]]\n\n===[[Commercial vehicle]]===\n* [[Mazda Bongo|Bongo Brawny]] \u2014 badge-engineered [[Toyota HiAce]]\n* [[Mazda Familia Van|Familia Van]] \u2014 badge-engineered [[Toyota Probox]]\n* [[Mazda Titan|Titan]] \u2014 [[truck]] \u2014 badge-engineered [[Isuzu Elf]]\n\n==Discontinued vehicles==\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n* 1931\u20131960 [[Mazda-Go]] three-wheel truck\n* 1958\u20131964 [[Mazda Romper|Romper/D1100/D1500/D2000]] truck\n* 1959\u20131969 [[Mazda K360|K360]] three-wheel truck\n* 1959\u20131971 [[Mazda T600|T600]] three-wheel truck\n* 1959\u20131971 [[Mazda T series|T1100/T1500/T2000]] three-wheel truck\n* 1960\u20131966 [[Mazda R360|R360]] [[kei car]] [[sedan (automobile)|sedan]]\n* 1961\u20131962 [[Mazda Carol|P360/P600 \"Carol\"]] kei car sedan\n* 1961\u20131966 [[Mazda Porter#B360/B600|B360/B600]] kei car pickup truck\n* 1961\u20132006 [[Mazda B-Series|B series/Proceed/REPU]] [[pickup truck]]\n* 1964\u20132003 [[Mazda Familia|Familia/323/Proteg\u00e9/R100]] [[compact car]]\n* 1965\u20131972 [[Mazda Light Bus| Light Bus Type A/C]] [[minibus]]\n* 1965\u20131977 [[Mazda Kraft|Kraft]] truck\n* 1966\u20131991 [[Mazda Luce|Luce/929/R130/RX-4/RX-9]] [[luxury car]]\n* 1967\u20131996 [[Mazda Cosmo|Cosmo/RX-5]] [[sports car]]\n* 1968\u20131980 [[Mazda Boxer|Boxer]] truck\n* 1968\u20131989 [[Mazda Porter|Porter]] small pickup truck\n* 1970\u20132002 [[Mazda Capella|Capella/626/RX-2/Cronos]] [[mid-siz