]] ([[Macmillan Publishers]])\n| divisions        =\n| subsid           =\n| homepage         = {{Official website|http://www.firstsecondbooks.com}}\n| footnotes        =\n| intl             =\n}}\n'''First Second Books''' is an American publisher of [[graphic novel]]s. An [[imprint (trade name)|imprint]] of [[Roaring Brook Press]], part of [[Holtzbrinck|Holtzbrinck Publishers]], First Second publishes fiction, biographies, personal memoirs, history, visual essays, and comics journalism.\n\n==History==\n{{Expand section|date=April 2010}}\nFirst Second launched in U.S. stores and online in May 2006.<ref>http://www.publishersweekly.com/pw/by-topic/industry-news/comics/article/70626-graphic-novel-publisher-first-second-celebrates-ten-years.html</ref>  It was distributed by [[Macmillan Publishers|Macmillan]] in the rest of the English-speaking world. After the merger in 2010, Macmillan distributes all of the books.\n\nIt is headed by editorial director [[Mark Siegel]].<ref>http://www.ew.com/article/2016/12/08/first-second-graphic-novels-fall-2017-cover-reveals</ref>\n\n==Titles==\n\n*Spring 2006\n**''A.L.I.E.E.E.N.'', by [[Lewis Trondheim]]\n**''[[Deogratias]]: A Tale of Rwanda'', by [[Jean-Philippe Stassen|Jean P. Stassen]]\n**''The Fate of the Artist'', by [[Eddie Campbell]]\n**''The Lost Colony v. 1: The Snodgrass Conspiracy'', by [[Grady Klein]]\n**''Sardine in Outer Space'', by [[Emmanuel Guibert]] and [[Joann Sfar]]\n**''Vampire Loves'', by [[Joann Sfar]]\n*Fall 2006\n**''[[American Born Chinese]]'', by [[Gene Luen Yang]]\n**''Journey Into Mohawk Country'', by Harmen Meyndertsz van den Bogaert and [[George O'Connor (comics)|George O'Connor]]\n**''[[The Kampung Boy]]'', by [[Lat (cartoonist)|Lat]]\n**''Klezmer'', by [[Joann Sfar]]\n**''Missouri Boy'', by [[Leland Myrick]]\n**''Sardine in Outer Space 2'', by Emmanuel Guibert and [[Joann Sfar]]\n*Spring 2007\n**''[[The Black Diamond Detective Agency]]'', by [[Eddie Campbell]]\n**''Garage Band'', by [[Gipi]]\n**''The 